  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2022.99.99-dev\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nCommit hash : \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen trying to retrieve a transaction by its transaction hash, and that transaction is a pending transaction provided by the rpcdaemon, the transaction details should be returned.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nPending transaction subscription works properly and provides a continuous flow of pending transactions, but all calls to eth_getTransaction are returning null.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n`web3.eth.subscribe('pendingTransactions')\r\n.on('connected', function(subscriptionId){\r\n    console.log(\"ReConnect at:\", Utils.getTime(), subscriptionId);\r\n})\r\n.on('data', (txHash) => {\r\n    setTimeout(async ()=>{\r\n        try{\r\n            let tx = await web3.eth.getTransaction(txHash);\r\n            console.log(txHash,tx);\r\n        }\r\n        catch(err){\r\n            console.log(err);\r\n        }\r\n    });\r\n})\r\n.on('error', function(error, receipt) { \r\n    console.log(error, receipt);\r\n});`\r\n\r\nYou should see a lot of transaction hashes, but only null values for the `web3.eth.getTransaction(txHash)` call.",
